19 years ago, nearly 3,000 people perished in the attacks of 9/11. Some of these people were emergency workers who sacrificed their lives to save others. We are surrounded by sacrificial individuals like those; men and women who respond daily to emergencies in our area. On Friday September 11th at 6:15 pm, the Wolsey-Wessington School will honor the first responders in our community and those visiting prior to our Homecoming Football Game. We are grateful to these courageous men and women who daily show selfless compassion as they put their lives in harms way to save and protect their fellow citizens. We ask that all first responders join us at the football field as we recognize and thank you with a small gift. The 7-12 band students will play a song in dedication to your patriotism.

First responders include: Emergency Medical Technicians (EMTs), Paramedics, Firefighters, Police Officers, Sheriffs/Sheriff Deputies, State Troopers, and any others who responds to a scene of emergency.

Due to the recent COVID 19 spike in Beadle County, we are STRONGLY ENCOURAGING voters to vote by Mail for the upcoming Primary Election June 2, 2020.

Absentee ballot applications can be found at
https://sdsos.gov/elections-voting/assets/AbsenteeBallotApplicationFillable.pdf.

Voters have until Monday, June 1, 2020 to request an Absentee Ballot.

All ballots need to be received by the Auditor’s Office by 7:00 p.m. Tuesday, June 2, 2020. It is $1.20 to mail the ballot.

For questions, please call the Beadle County Auditor’s Office 605-353-8400. This message has been brought to you by the Beadle County Auditor's Office.

Attention W-W School District voters, to vote for the school board election you will need to vote by absentee ballot or in person at the following locations-
Beadle County-Madison School in Huron
Hand County-Doug Schiltz farm

There will not be a polling place in the towns of Wolsey or Wessington.

Each registered voter received information in the mail concerning absentee voting. If you have any questions about the form, please call Amy or Mrs. Boomsma-Kelsey at the school at 883-4221. The request to absentee vote needs to be mailed soon if that is your plan. Let us know if we can answer any questions for you and please spread the word. Thank you!

WINNERS IN THE MRS. FAUTH IS BORED COMPETITION

Thank you to everyone who entered the Mrs. Fauth is Bored writing competition. It was tough to pick the winners, but I have made some choices:
First place goes to Payson Gohn, for his "alternate alphabet"--very creative
Second place goes to Ethan Nelson for his ability to guess some of the things I would like to do

Honorable Mention goes to Faith Nelson for suggesting I try to get along better with Priscilla (my computer) and Eric Klanchnik who not only suggested I write a play, but gave me a premise for one.
I have no idea when prizes will be given, but these people will be receiving something--probably when I see them in the fall!
Thanks to everyone for making it a fun competition, and congratulations to the winners!

GRAB AND GO MEALS
In the event that Wolsey-Wessington School is closed next week, we will be offering 4 breakfast/4 lunch Grab and Go meals to students in grades PreK-12 to be picked up at the main entrance of the school on Monday, March 30 from 11:00-12:00. The students must be present in the vehicle when the meals are picked up. We will have parents pull up to the main entrance and treat it like a drive through so you don't have to get out of your vehicle. There will be no delivery of meals.

GRAB AND GO MEALS
In the event that Wolsey-Wessington School is closed next week, we will be offering 4 breakfast/4 lunch Grab and Go meals to students in grades PreK-12 to be picked up at the main entrance of the school on Monday, March 30 from 11:00-12:00. The students must be present in the vehicle when the meals are picked up. We will have parents pull up to the main entrance and treat it like a drive through so you don't have to get out of your vehicle. There will be no delivery of meals.

To sign up your children for next week's meals, please email jennifer.boomsma@k12.sd.us or text 605-350-0826 BEFORE 11:00 AM tomorrow morning (March 24).

Thank you for all of your cooperation today in the delivery of materials. Thank you to the staff for all of your teamwork that made this possible. We hope all of you stay healthy and safe.
